==Trivia==
*Each of the three kings' names come from a Latin word: ''supremus'' means 'highest', ''primus'' means 'first' and ''rex'' means 'King'.
*The kings are an allegory for the game Rock, Paper, Scissors: each of the kings' initials corresponds to one of Rock (Rex), Paper (Prime) or Scissors (Supreme), with their attack styles corresponding to which of the three options beats which, as per the [[combat triangle]].

